20in%20water%20consumption%20in%20its%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAs%20the%20AI%20arms%20race%20heats%20up%2C%20it%20may%20only%20get%20worse.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20just%20published%20its%202023%20environmental%20report%2C%20and%20one%20thing%20is%20for%20certain%3A%20The%20company's%20water%20use%20is%20soaring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gstatic.com%2Fgumdrop%2Fsustainability%2Fgoogle-2023-environmental-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20internet%20giant%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20consumed%205.6%20billion%20gallons%20of%20water%20in%202022%2C%20the%20equivalent%20of%2037%20golf%20courses.%20Most%20of%20that%20--%205.2%20billion%20gallons%20--%20was%20used%20for%20the%20company's%20data%20centers%2C%20a%2020%25%20increase%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gstatic.com%2Fgumdrop%2Fsustainability%2F2022-us-data-center-water.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20amount%20Google%20reported%20the%20year%20prior%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20provide%20a%20stark%20reminder%20of%20the%20environmental%20cost%20of%20running%20huge%20data%20centers%2C%20which%20often%20require%20vast%20amounts%20of%20water%20to%20stay%20cool.%20And%20as%20Google%20and%20every%20other%20tech%20company%20in%20the%20AI%20arms%20race%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-ai-artificial-intelligence-farmland-power-2023-7%5C%22%3Espeed%20to%20build%20new%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20water%20they%20consume%20will%20very%20likely%20keep%20rising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2020%25%20jump%20in%20water%20consumption%20is%20roughly%20in%20line%20with%20the%20increase%20in%20Google's%20compute%20capacity%2C%20which%20has%20been%20largely%20driven%20by%20AI%2C%20said%20Shaolei%20Ren%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20electrical%20and%20computer%20engineering%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Riverside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Ren%20said%20he's%20skeptical%20that%20this%20increase%20is%20sustainable%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%20even%20with%20Google's%20commitment%20to%20replenish%20water%20to%20offset%20its%20usage.%C2%A0%26quot%3BIt%20just%20makes%20their%20water%20accounting%20looks%20nicer%2C%20but%20the%20water%20is%20still%20consumed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20said%20it%20has%20targeted%202030%20as%20a%20deadline%20to%20replenish%20120%25%20of%20the%20freshwater%20it%20consumes%20across%20its%20offices%20and%20data%20centers.%20Right%20now%20it's%20replenishing%20just%206%25%2C%20according%20to%20its%20own%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20the%20water%20Google%20is%20consuming%20right%20now%20is%20%26quot%3Bpotable%2C%26quot%3B%20clean%20enough%20to%20be%20used%20as%20drinking%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20latest%20report%2C%20Google%20said%20it%20takes%20%26quot%3Blocal%20water%20stress%26quot%3B%20(another%20way%20of%20saying%20scarcity)%20into%20account%2C%20and%20said%2082%25%20of%20its%20freshwater%20withdrawals%20in%202022%20came%20from%20regions%20with%20low%20water%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20remaining%2018%25%2C%20it%20says%20it's%20%26quot%3Bexploring%20new%20partnerships%20and%20opportunities%26quot%3B%20to%20improve%20watershed%20health%2C%20but%20it%20may%20face%20increased%20resistance%20as%20more%20places%20face%20water%20shortages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farizona-running-out-of-water-data-centers-blame-microsoft-google-2023-6%5C%22%3EGoogle%20planned%20a%20data%20center%20in%20Mesa%2C%20Arizona%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20got%20a%20guarantee%20of%20up%20to%204%20million%20gallons%20of%20water%20a%20day.%C2%A0But%20as%20Insider's%20Alistair%20Barr%20recently%20pointed%20out%2C%20Arizona%20is%20already%20facing%20a%20water%20shortage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com