li%3EOhio%20voters%20appear%20primed%20to%20pass%20an%20abortion%20rights%20constitutional%20amendment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAccording%20to%20a%20new%20poll%2C%2058%25%20of%20likely%20Ohio%20voters%20would%20vote%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20amendment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESupporters%20of%20the%20proposed%20amendment%20will%20find%20out%20shortly%20if%20they%20gathered%20enough%20signatures%20to%20make%20the%20ballot.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOhio%20voters%20appear%20ready%20to%20back%20a%20potential%20abortion%20rights%20constitutional%20amendment%20by%20large%20margins%2C%20underlying%20how%20the%20post-Roe%20reaction%20continues%20to%20animate%20voters%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2F07%2F24%2Fohioans-back-abortion-rights-amendment-a-test-case-for-other-states%2F70413318007%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20a%20USA%20Today%2FSuffolk%20University%20poll%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%2058%25%20of%20voters%20support%20a%20state%20constitutional%20amendment%20that%20would%20protect%20the%20right%20to%20an%20abortion%20up%20to%20the%20point%20of%20viability.%20Thirty-two%20percent%20of%20voters%20oppose%20the%20measure.%20Just%20like%20in%20other%20states%2C%20the%20measure%20is%20showing%20support%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum.%20The%20poll%20found%20that%20one-third%20of%20GOP%20voters%20would%20back%20the%20amendment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOhio%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Frank%20LaRose%20must%20declare%20by%20tomorrow%20whether%20the%20abortion%20rights%20measure%20has%20enough%20signatures%20to%20qualify%20for%20the%20November%20ballot.%20Right%20now%2C%20most%20abortions%20in%20Ohio%20are%20legal%20up%20until%2022%20weeks%20of%20pregnancy%2C%20but%20that%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statenews.org%2Fgovernment-politics%2F2023-04-07%2Fohio-governor-says-lawmakers-should-clarify-six-week-abortion-ban-now-on-hold-by-a-court%5C%22%3Eonly%20because%20a%20county%20judge%20paused%20an%20abortion%20ban%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Republican%20Gov.%20Mike%20DeWine%20had%20signed%20a%20ban%20that%20would%20effectively%20outlaw%20most%20abortions%20after%20six%20weeks%20of%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20another%20potential%20wrinkle%20looming.%20The%20Republican-controlled%20legislature%20pushed%20for%20a%20special%20election%20next%20month%20that%20would%20raise%20the%20current%20threshold%20for%20constitutional%20amendments%20from%20a%C2%A0simple%20majority%20to%2060%25%2C%20underlining%20how%20Republicans%20and%20anti-abortion%20advocates%20have%20turned%20to%20other%20methods%20as%20a%20way%20to%20try%20to%20stop%20the%20wave%20of%20abortion%20rights%20ballot%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20effort%20to%20raise%20the%20threshold%20might%20backfire%20too.%20The%20poll%20found%20that%2057%25%20of%20voters%20oppose%20raising%20the%20threshold%20that%20would%20apply%20to%20all%20measures%20going%20forward%20while%20only%2026%25%20of%20voters%20support%20it.%20Abortion-related%20amendments%20may%20have%20dominated%20recent%20headlines%2C%20but%20raising%20the%20threshold%20would%20affect%20much%20more%20than%20just%20that.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20states%20have%20addressed%20marijuana%20legalization%2C%20raising%20the%20minimum%20wage%2C%20and%20other%20questions%20on%20the%20ballot.%20Ohioans%20may%20also%20vote%20on%20recreational%20marijuana%20this%20November%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncsl.org%2Felections-and-campaigns%2Finitiative-and-referendum-states%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20National%20Conference%20of%20State%20Legislatures%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20almost%20every%20state%20provides%20for%20some%20type%20of%20ballot%20question%20either%20through%20citizen-proposed%20initiatives%20of%20new%20laws%2C%20popular%20referendums%20on%20just%20passed%20laws%2C%C2%A0%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20those%20methods.%20Some%20initiatives%20are%20then%20directly%20decided%20based%20on%20the%20vote%2C%20while%20others%20involve%20the%20state%20legislature.%20The%20Mississippi%20Supreme%20Court%20effectively%20voided%20its%20initiative%20process%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabortion-access-ballot-initiatives-which-states-2024-2023-2%5C%22%3EAs%20Insider%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20abortion%20rights%20measures%20could%20prove%20to%20deliver%20major%20political%20benefits%20to%20Democrats.%20During%20the%202022%20midterms%2C%20abortion%20rights%20groups%20passed%20every%20state%20measure%20they%20sought%20and%20also%20beat%20back%20efforts%20to%20restrict%20abortion%20access.%20Their%20success%20underlined%20how%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20decision%20to%20gut%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%20triggered%20a%20massive%20uproar%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20USA%20Today%2FSuffolk%20University%20poll%20of%20500%20likely%20Ohio%20voters%20was%20conducted%20from%20July%209%20to%2012.%20Voters%20were%20reached%20via%20traditional%20landlines%20and%20by%20cell%20phone.%20The%20overall%20margin%20of%20error%20is%20%2B%2F-%204.4%20percentage%20points.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fohio-voters-are-primed-to-back-abortion-rights-measure-poll-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690232426000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64bee451bea34400196060d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fohio-voters-are-primed-to-back-abortion-rights-measure-poll-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Supporters%20of%20the%20proposed%20amendment%20will%20find%20out%20shortly%20if%20they%20gathered%20enough%20signatures%20to%20make%20the%20ballot.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A80%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsid