les%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FForest%2520(Conservation)%2520Amendment%2520Bill%2C%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBill%20to%20amend%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Ever%20since%20the%20amendment%20was%20first%20proposed%2C%20it%20has%20garnered%20stiff%20opposition%20on%20a%20host%20of%20issues%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Fharyana%2Fsuicidal-for-forests-in-haryana-fca-bill-draws-flak-from-activists-510075%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Evast%20tracts%20of%20forestlands%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20losing%20the%20protective%20cover%20of%20the%20Act%20by%20narrowing%20down%20the%20definition%20of%20what%20constitutes%20a%20forest%2C%20exceptions%20from%20forest%20clearance%20for%20linear%20infrastructure%20up%20to%20100%20kms%20from%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20border%2C%20and%20according%20exemptions%20to%20various%20forest%20diversion%20activities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20Science%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fobjections-to-proposed-changes-to-forest-conservation-act-pour-in-from-all-corners%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epreviously%20documented%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20opposition%20to%20the%20bill%20via%20submissions%20made%20by%20conservationists%2C%20tribal%20groups%2C%20officers%20of%20the%20Indian%20Forest%20Service%2C%20and%20environmental%20lawyers%20and%20activists%20to%20the%20joint%20parliament%20committee%20(JPC)%20that%20was%20constituted%20to%20assess%20the%20proposed%20amendments.%20Rajendra%20Agrawal%2C%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20MP%20from%20Meerut%20is%20the%20chairperson%20of%20the%20JPC.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20July%2011%2C%20the%20JPC%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fsci-tech%2Fenergy-and-environment%2Fsix-opposition-members-file-dissent-notes-on-forest-conservation-bill%2Farticle67067932.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eofficially%20cleared%20the%20bill%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20without%20proposing%20a%20single%20change%20while%20individual%20members%20filed%20dissent%20notes.%20This%20is%20despite%20the%20environment%20ministry%20offering%20inadequate%20justifications%20for%20the%20amendments%20made%20during%20the%20JPC%20process%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1fM92FL_U0eeOyopOH16mfPa3a62WD7kg%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dsharing%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20confidential%20document%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20accessed%20by%20%3Cem%3EWire%20Science%3C%2Fem%3E%20shows.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fembeds%2F660873855%2Fcontent%3Fstart_page%3D1%26view_mode%3Dscroll%26access_key%3Dkey-M8RbekFnY7uGKlgsn8sA%5C%22%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20data-auto-height%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20data-aspect-ratio%3D%5C%221.645985401459854%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Clause%20by%20Clause%20Comments%20of%20Ministry%20With%20Circulation%20Letter%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F660873855%2FClause-by-Clause-Comments-of-Ministry-With-Circulation-Letter%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20Clause%20by%20Clause%20Comments%20of%20Ministry%20With%20Circulation%20Letter%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EClause%20by%20Clause%20Comments%20o%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fuser%2F286754081%2FThe-Wire%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20The%20Wire's%20profile%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShared%20with%20the%20JPC%20in%20mid-June%2C%20the%20document%20lays%20down%20clause-by-clause%20reasonings%20and%20justifications%20of%20the%20ministry%20for%20bringing%20forth%20the%20amendment%2C%20in%20response%20to%20suggestions%20and%20comments%20gathered%20by%20the%20JPC.%20The%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20arguments%20do%20not%20hold%20water%2C%20experts%20pointed%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%2C%20consider%20how%20the%20ministry%20claims%20in%20the%20document%20that%20provisions%20of%20the%20Act%20will%20be%20applicable%20on%20%E2%80%9Crevenue%20forest%20land%2C%20private%20forest%20land%2C%20and%20other%20land%20recorded%20as%20forest%20in%20the%20records%E2%80%9D%20in%20response%20to%20concerns%20that%20many%20eco-sensitive%20areas%20which%20haven%E2%80%99t%20been%20recorded%20as%20forests%20in%20government%20records%20(like%20large%20sections%20of%20the%20Aravalli%20range)%20will%20no%20longer%20require%20forest%20clearance%20and%20be%20open%20for%20commercialisation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20case%2C%20why%20not%20explicitly%20mention%20%5Bthat%20the%20Act%20will%20apply%20to%20across%20such%20lands%5D%20in%20the%20Bill%3F%20Tomorrow%20when%20a%20case%20comes%20up%20before%20the%20courts%2C%20judgements%20will%20be%20passed%20based%20on%20the%20Act%2C%20not%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20comments%20during%20the%20JPC%20process%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ritwick%20Dutta%2C%20an%20environmental%20lawyer%20and%20co-founder%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthelifeindia.org.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ELegal%20Initiative%20for%20Forests%20and%20Environment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(LIFE).%20At%20present%2C%20the%20Bill%20states%20the%20Act%20will%20only%20apply%20to%20lands%20that%20have%20been%20declared%20or%20notified%20as%20a%20forest%20under%20relevant%20laws%20or%20have%20been%20recorded%20as%20forests%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20records.%20But%2C%20Dutta%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Himalaya%20and%20the%20Brahmaputra%20are%20the%20Himalaya%20and%20the%20Brahmaputra%20regardless%20of%20whether%20they%20are%20notified%20as%20such.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ministry%20has%20also%20claimed%20that%20forest%20lands%20have%20been%20identified%20by%20expert%20committees%20at%20the%20state%20and%20Union%20territory%20level%2C%20in%20pursuance%20of%20the%201996%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F187366700%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ET.N.%20Godavarman%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20case%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20same%20have%20already%20been%20taken%20on%20record%20and%20hence%20the%20provision%20of%20the%20Act%20will%20remain%20applicable%20on%20such%20lands%20also%E2%80%9D.%20Broadly%2C%20the%20case%20was%20filed%20in%20view%20of%20timber%20logging%20in%20Nilgiri%20hills%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20wherein%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20%E2%80%98forest%E2%80%99%20includes%20all%20land%20recorded%20as%20a%20forest%20in%20governmental%20records%20regardless%20of%20its%20ownership%20and%20also%20%E2%80%98deemed%20forests%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20are%20not%20recorded%20as%20forests%20but%20satisfy%20the%20dictionary%20meaning%20of%20%E2%80%98forests%E2%80%99%20i.e.%20any%20large%20area%20with%20significant%20tree%20cover%20and%20undergrowth.%20The%20court%20also%20ordered%20state%20governments%20to%20identify%20forests%20as%20per%20this%20definition%20in%20their%20respective%20states.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20stance%20that%20forests%20have%20been%20identified%20by%20relevant%20expert%20committees%20ignores%20the%20fact%20that%20some%20committees%20are%20yet%20to%20finalise%20the%20process%20of%20identification%20of%20forestlands%20in%20some%20states.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EPrerna%20Bindra%2C%20a%20conservationist%20and%20former%20member%20of%20the%20National%20Board%20for%20Wildlife%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20many%20states%20have%20submitted%20these%20expert%20committee%20reports%2C%20and%20if%20so%2C%20whether%20they%20have%20followed%20the%20parameters%20set%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20identifying%20such%20areas.%20Has%20the%20%5Benvironment%5D%20ministry%20reviewed%20the%20process%20to%20understand%20whether%20it%20was%20scientific%2C%20exhaustive%2C%20and%20reflects%20ground%20realities%20%E2%80%93%20or%20not%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EComments%20and%20suggestions%20discarded%2C%20govt%20pushes%20through%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20core%20criticism%20is%20that%20the%20ministry%20is%20relying%20excessively%20on%20the%20rule-making%20powers%20of%20the%20executive%20to%20justify%20the%20amendments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20comments%2C%20the%20environment%20ministry%20has%20repeatedly%20included%20references%20to%20%E2%80%9Cterms%20and%20conditions%E2%80%9D%20that%20are%20as%20yet%20undefined%20to%20carve%20out%20exemptions%20from%20forest%20clearances%20for%20purposes%20like%20border%20infrastructure.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20ambiguity%20leaves%20room%20for%20dilutions%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Meenakshi%20Kapoor%2C%20an%20independent%20researcher%20working%20on%20environmental%20policy.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20has%20also%20included%20an%20amendment%20under%20Section%206%20of%20the%20Act%20to%20say%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20issue%20directions%20as%20may%20be%20necessary%20for%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%C2%A0%20Act.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20recourse%20to%20delegated%20legislation%20which%20is%20a%20bad%20feature%20of%20any%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shashank%20Pandey%2C%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvidhilegalpolicy.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVidhi%20Centre%20for%20Legal%20Policy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ministry%20has%20also%20put%20forth%20unsubstantiated%20views%20in%20the%20confidential%20JPC%20document.%20Elaborating%20on%20its%20stand%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20need%20to%20chalk%20out%20exemptions%20for%20defence%20projects%20in%20border%20areas%2C%20the%20ministry%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CDefence%20projects%20which%20are%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20a%20time%20bound%20manner%20often%20gets%20delayed%20due%20to%20length%20(sic)%20procedures%20and%20documentations%20involved%20in%20the%20process%20of%20approval.%E2%80%9D%20But%20where%20is%20the%20evidence%20for%20this%3F%20Kapoor%20asked.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ministry%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20exemption%20will%20not%20be%20made%20available%20to%20private%20entities.%20But%20this%20assurance%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20go%20far%20enough%20to%20address%20environmental%20concerns.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20Uttarakhand%20and%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20linear%20infrastructure%20projects%20by%20the%20National%20Highways%20Authority%20of%20India%20are%20causing%20deforestation%20and%20triggering%20landslides%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Manshi%20Asher%2C%20a%20researcher%20and%20activist%20associated%20with%20Himdhara%20Collective%20based%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20public%20submissions%20made%20to%20the%20JPC%20also%20highlight%20that%20exemptions%20would%20mean%20%E2%80%9Cno%20impact%20assessment%20or%20any%20kind%20of%20regulatory%20oversight%20on%20the%20loss%20of%20habitats%20and%20species%E2%80%9D%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20northeastern%20states%20where%20the%20exemption%20regarding%20100%20kms%20would%20cover%20almost%20the%20entire%20region.%20Exemptions%20are%20also%20prone%20to%20misuse%2C%20the%20submissions%20state.%20Interestingly%2C%20many%20BJP-ruled%20states%20in%20the%20northeast%20like%20Sikkim%2C%20Mizoram%2C%20Tripura%2C%20and%20Nagaland%2C%20and%20also%20others%20like%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20have%20opposed%20the%20100%20kms%20exemption%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1KR166CGy8HGKhw4mNLaXfM1h4wcrUYoI%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dsharing%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efinal%20JPC%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20tabled%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%2020th%20July.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20internal%20JPC%20document%20also%20shows%20that%20the%20ministry%20has%20deflected%20from%20answering%20why%20it%20has%20proposed%20a%20change%20to%20the%20title%20of%20the%20Act%20to%20Hindi%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Van%20Sanrakshan%20Evam%20Samvardhan%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20against%20linguistic%20federalist%20principles%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%20In%20response%20to%20a%20comment%20sent%20to%20the%20JPC%20to%20this%20effect%2C%20the%20ministry%20went%20on%20a%20tangent%20to%20explain%2C%20%E2%80%9CDynamic%20changes%20in%20the%20policies%20and%20programmes%20call%20for%20more%20efficient%20management%20of%20our%20forest%20resources%20to%20increase%20their%20productivity.%20Besides%20this%2C%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20global%20challenges%20viz.%20carbon%20neutrality%2C%20Nationally%20Determined%20Contributions%20(NDC)%2C%20it%20is%20necessary%20to%20increase%20the%20green%20cover%2C%20striking%20a%20balance%20between%20ecological%20stability%20and%20economic%20aspirations%2C%20etc.%20Therefore%2C%20considering%20the%20aforementioned%20facts%2C%20it%20has%20been%20proposed%20to%20assign%20a%20self-contained%20name%20to%20the%20Act.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20self-contained%20name%20of%20the%20Act%20could%20have%20been%20in%20English%20also%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dutta%20pointed%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20JPC%20has%20endorsed%20the%20amendment%20bill%20in%20its%20entirety.%20The%20environment%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20comments%20reflected%20in%20the%20final%20JPC%20report%20also%20show%20that%20its%20stand%20on%20the%20aforementioned%20issues%20has%20been%20the%20same%20even%20after%20deliberations%20with%20the%20JPC.%20A%20question%20that%20arises%20then%20is%20to%20what%20extent%20the%20JPC%20was%20a%20consultative%20process%20where%20feedback%20was%20considered%20and%20deliberated%20upon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20JPC%20has%20only%20undertaken%20mechanical%20work.%20It%20has%20collected%20comments%20%5Bfrom%20the%20public%5D%20and%20sent%20them%20to%20the%20ministry%20saying%20%E2%80%98answer%20it%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6%20it%20has%20not%20independently%20assessed%20the%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Debadityo%20Sinha%2C%20Senior%20Resident%20Fellow%20and%20Lead%20of%20the%20Climate%20%26amp%3B%20Ecosystems%20team%20at%20Vidhi%20Centre%20for%20Legal%20Policy.%20Sinha%20also%20questioned%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20parliamentary%20process%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20seemed%20like%20they%20were%20only%20fulfilling%20a%20formality%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20application%20of%20mind%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERishika%20Pardikar%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690211732000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F19200957%2Fimage-1146.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchanges-to-forest-conservation-act-heres-what-an-internal-document-of-the-govt-reveals%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20stiff%20opposition%20from%20several%20quarters%2C%20a%20Bill%20to%20amend%20the%20conservation%20law%20was%20tabled%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20July%2020.%20Surprisingly%2C%20a%20joint%20parliamentary%20committee%20had%20also%20cleared%20the%20Bill%20without%20proposing%20a%20single%20change%20even%20after%20individual%20members%20filed%20'dissent%20notes'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchanges-to-forest-conservation-act-heres-what-an-internal-document-of-the-govt-reveals%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Protests%20in%20Israel%20as%20controversial%20change%20to%20judges'%20power%20is%20approved%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690211340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F768x432%2Fskynews-jerusalem-israel_6229016.jpg%3F20230724162432%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fprotests-in-israel-as-parliament-approves-key-part-of-controversial-changes-to-justice-system-12926750%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Israel's%20parliament%20has%20signed%20off%20a%20key%20part%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu's%20controversial%20plan%20to%20reshape%20the%20justice%20system.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A55%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fprotests-in-israel-as-parliament-approves-key-part-of-controversial-changes-to-justice-system-12926750%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fprotests-in-israel-as-parliament-approves-key-part-of-controversial-changes-to-justice-system-12926750%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fprotests-in-israel-as-parliament-approves-key-part-of-controversial-changes-to-justice-system-12926750%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel%20judicial%20reform%3A%20What%20is%20the%20crisis%20about%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690210624000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FEE2D%2Fproduction%2F_129137906_mediaitem129137905.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-65086871%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Israel%20has%20been%20gripped%20by%20months%20of%20mass%20protests%20against%20government%20plans.%20Here's%20why.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A614%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-65086871%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-65086871.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-65086871.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reservation%20of%20J%26K%20Assembly%20Seats%20for%20Kashmiri%20Migrants%2C%20Refugees%20Sparks%20Nomination%20Debate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F04090458%2F2022_10img03_Oct_2022_PTI10_03_.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESrinagar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20Union%20government%20is%20planning%20to%20introduce%20a%20Bill%20in%20parliament%20to%20reserve%20three%20seats%20in%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20for%20Kashmiri%20migrants%20and%20refugees%20from%20the%20Pakistan-occupied%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20(PoJK).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20take%20the%20number%20of%20nominated%20seats%20in%20the%20unicameral%20House%20to%20five%20as%20two%20seats%20were%20already%20reserved%20for%20women%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20claims%20that%20the%20Bill%20is%20aimed%20at%20%E2%80%9Cpreserving%20the%20political%20rights%20of%20these%20communities%20as%20well%20as%20for%20their%20overall%20social%20and%20economic%20development%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20within%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20political%20circles%2C%20it%20is%20being%20debated%20whether%20the%20Union%20territory%E2%80%99s%20elected%20government%20would%20have%20a%20role%20in%20making%20these%20nominations%2C%20or%20would%20these%20seats%20be%20used%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20subvert%20public%20mandate%20and%20destabilise%20elected%20regimes%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20akin%20to%20what%20happened%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fnew-jk-to-be-like-puducherry-here-is-how-indias-new-union-territory-jk-will-function%2Farticleshow%2F70532687.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3EPuducherry%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20proposed%20Bill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Eaccessed%20documents%20that%20show%20that%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%20provides%20for%20the%20nomination%20of%20three%20MLAs%20%E2%80%93%20two%20from%20the%20Kashmiri%20migrant%20community%20and%20one%20from%20the%20displaced%20persons%20of%20PoJK%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20of%20the%20UT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20Bill%20specifies%20that%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%93%20who%20is%20appointed%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20%E2%80%93%20would%20nominate%20these%20MLAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202019%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20retained%20the%20provision%20of%20nominating%20two%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20of%20the%20UT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNotwithstanding%20anything%20in%20sub-section%20(3)%20of%20section%2014%2C%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20of%20the%20successor%20Union%20territory%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20may%20nominate%20two%20members%20to%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20to%20give%20representation%20to%20women%2C%20if%20in%20his%20opinion%2C%20women%20are%20not%20adequately%20represented%20in%20the%20legislative%20assembly%2C%E2%80%9D%20reads%20section%2015%20of%20the%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20provision%20also%20existed%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20provided%20that%20two%20women%20can%20be%20nominated%20to%20the%20assembly%20by%20the%20governor.%20The%20nomination%20would%20occur%20if%20the%20governor%20believed%20that%20the%20women%20are%20not%20adequately%20represented%20in%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20governor%20would%20then%20make%20these%20nominations%20on%20recommendations%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%E2%80%99s%20elected%20government%20as%20he%20was%20bound%20to%20do%20so%20under%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20shall%20be%20a%20council%20of%20ministers%20with%20the%20chief%20minister%20at%20the%20head%20to%20aid%20and%20advise%20the%20governor%20in%20the%20exercise%20of%20his%20functions.%20All%20functions%20of%20the%20governor%20except%20those%20under%20sections%2036%2C%2038%20and%2092%20shall%20be%20exercised%20by%20him%20only%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%E2%80%9D%20read%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20constitution%20whose%20key%20provisions%20were%20repealed%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20will%20have%20the%20power%20to%20nominate%20these%20MLAs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bigger%20question%20is%2C%20whether%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20would%20consult%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20council%20of%20ministers%20or%20the%20chief%20minister%20before%20making%20nominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20cursory%20look%20at%20the%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019%20and%20the%20proposed%20Bill%20suggests%20that%20the%20specific%20authority%20to%20nominate%20these%20MLAs%20in%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20lies%20with%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Reorganisation%20Act%20further%20reveals%20that%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20bound%20to%20go%20by%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%20on%20the%20nomination%20of%20the%20MLAs%2C%20as%20the%20law%20restricts%20the%20role%20of%20the%20elected%20government%20in%20advising%20him%20on%20the%20matters%20over%20which%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20assembly%20has%20powers%20to%20enact%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20shall%20be%20a%20council%20of%20ministers%20consisting%20of%20not%20more%20than%20ten%20percent%20of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20members%20in%20the%20legislative%20assembly%2C%20with%20the%20chief%20minister%20at%20the%20head%20to%20aid%20and%20advise%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20in%20the%20exercise%20of%20his%20functions%20in%20relation%20to%20matters%20with%20respect%20to%20which%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20has%20power%20to%20make%20laws%20except%20in%20so%20far%20as%20he%20is%20required%20by%20or%20under%20this%20Act%20to%20act%20in%20his%20discretion%20or%20by%20or%20under%20any%20law%20to%20exercise%20any%20judicial%20or%20quasi-judicial%20functions%2C%E2%80%9D%20reads%20section%2053%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Article%20239A%2C%20the%20parliament%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20enact%20a%20body%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20elected%2C%20or%20partly%20nominated%20and%20partly%20elected%20%E2%80%93%20to%20function%20as%20a%20legislature%20for%20a%20UT.%20Since%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20assembly%20has%20no%20powers%20to%20enact%20a%20law%20for%20its%20composition%2C%20it%20means%20that%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20would%20not%20be%20required%20to%20consult%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%20while%20nominating%20MLAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F95239810%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EK.%20Lakshminarayanan%20versus%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20held%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20is%20not%20required%20to%20consult%20the%20elected%20government%20for%20nominating%20members%20to%20the%20Puducherry%20assembly.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20court%20emphasised%20that%20the%20nominated%20members%20have%20the%20same%20right%20to%20vote%20as%20the%20elected%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019%20also%20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20nominated%20members%20have%20voting%20rights%20on%20all%20issues%2C%20including%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20and%20budget%2C%20as%20the%20Act%20treats%20elected%20and%20nominated%20members%20equally%20in%20terms%20of%20voting%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSave%20as%20otherwise%20provided%20in%20this%20Act%2C%20all%20questions%20at%20any%20sitting%20of%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20shall%20be%20determined%20by%20a%20majority%20of%20votes%20of%20the%20members%20present%20and%20voting%2C%20other%20than%20the%20Speaker%20or%20person%20acting%20as%20such%2C%E2%80%9D%20reads%20section%2025%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fexplainer-the-major-changes-to-jammu-and-kashmir-as-it-becomes-a-union-territory%5C%22%3EExplainer%3A%20The%20Major%20Changes%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20It%20Becomes%20a%20Union%20Territory%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98A%20subversion%20of%20public%20mandate%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20analyst%20Zaffar%20Choudhary%20said%20that%20the%20nomination%20process%20would%20have%20an%20unfair%20bearing%20on%20public%20mandate%20if%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20has%20powers%20to%20nominate%20MLAs%20before%20floor%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20law%20is%20not%20very%20clear%20about%20who%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20nominate%20such%20members%20to%20the%20assembly.%20If%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20does%20this%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20elected%20government%2C%20then%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20fair%20process.%20However%2C%20if%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20is%20empowered%20to%20nominate%20members%20to%20the%20assembly%20before%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20elected%20government%2C%20it%20will%20have%20an%20unfair%20bearing%20on%20the%20public%20mandate.%20Such%20nomination%20of%20members%20with%20voting%20powers%20can%20potentially%20change%20the%20floor%20arithmetic%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20amendment%20to%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019%20%E2%80%93%20which%20increases%20the%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20%E2%80%93%20aligns%20with%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20delimitation%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20bring%20a%20Bill%20on%20the%20matter%20is%20indicative%20of%20the%20possibility%20of%20preparing%20for%20the%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EM.Y.%20Tarigami%2C%20four-time%20MLA%20and%20senior%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20leader%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20is%20%E2%80%98unconstitutional%20and%20illegitimate%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20that%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%202019%20is%20not%20in%20tune%20with%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%20They%20should%20wait%20for%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20before%20going%20ahead%20with%20the%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20proposed%20legislation%20mocks%20the%20plight%20of%20the%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%20and%20the%20refugees.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20should%20have%20carved%20out%20exclusive%20seats%20for%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%20and%20PoJK%20refugees%20in%20Jammu%20during%20the%20delimitation%20process.%20These%20nominated%20members%20will%20be%20representatives%20of%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20rather%20than%20their%20communities.%20If%20they%20were%20so%20concerned%20about%20their%20political%20rights%2C%20they%20should%20have%20given%20them%20the%20right%20to%20elect%20their%20representatives%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENational%20Conference%20MP%20from%20south%20Kashmir%2C%20Justice%20(retd.)%20Hasnain%20Masoodi%2C%20said%20that%20they%20would%20wait%20for%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20be%20inappropriate%20on%20part%20of%20the%20Centre%20to%20bring%20such%20a%20Bill%20at%20this%20time%2C%20as%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20set%20to%20hear%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20politician%2C%20wishing%20not%20to%20be%20named%2C%20said%20that%20such%20a%20move%20would%20mean%20a%20subversion%20of%20public%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20not%20averse%20to%20political%20empowerment%20of%20these%20communities%2C%20but%20such%20a%20move%20would%20mean%20that%20the%20government%20in%20New%20Delhi%20would%20have%20partial%20control%20on%20the%20legislative%20assembly%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-amendment-reorganisation-jammu-kashmir-unconstitutional-violate-fundamental-rights-petition-supreme-court%5C%22%3EIs%20the%20Division%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20Unconstitutional%3F%20Here%E2%80%99s%20What%20a%20Petition%20in%20SC%20Says%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKashmiri%20migrants%2C%20displaced%20persons%20from%20PoJK%20and%20their%20representation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20the%20outbreak%20of%20armed%20militancy%20in%20Kashmir%20in%201989%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Kashmiri%20Hindu%20families%20had%20migrated%20from%20their%20places%20of%20residence%20to%20Jammu%20and%20other%20cities.%20They%20are%20called%20Kashmiri%20migrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%2046%2C517%20families%2C%20comprising%201%2C58%2C976%20people%2C%20are%20registered%20as%20Kashmiri%20migrants%20with%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20government.%20They%20also%20comprise%20a%20few%20hundred%20Sikh%20and%20Muslim%20families%20who%20had%20migrated%20to%20Jammu%20during%20that%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%201957%2C%20one%20or%20two%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%20had%20been%20elected%20to%20the%20assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20till%202002.%20Even%20after%20the%20armed%20conflict%20broke%20out%20in%20the%20region%20in%201989%2C%20members%20from%20the%20Kashmiri%20Pandit%20community%20had%20managed%20to%20get%20elected%20from%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201996%2C%20P.L.%20Handoo%20of%20the%20National%20Conference%20got%20elected%20from%20Habba%20Kadal%20and%20became%20a%20cabinet%20minister%20in%20the%20Farooq%20Abdullah-led%20government.%20In%202002%2C%20Raman%20Matto%2C%20who%20fought%20as%20an%20independent%20candidate%2C%20won%20from%20Habba%20Kadal%20and%20became%20a%20minister%20of%20state%20in%20the%20Mufti%20Muhammad%20Sayeed-led%20government.%20In%20the%202008%20and%202014%20elections%2C%20no%20Kashmiri%20Pandit%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20displaced%20persons%20are%20those%20who%20have%20migrated%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20occupied%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20to%20J%26amp%3BK%20in%20the%201947-48%2C%201965%20and%201971%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20official%20records%2C%20there%20are%20a%20total%20number%20of%2041%2C844%20such%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20state%20subjects%2C%20the%20PoJK%20refugees%20had%20all%20political%20rights%20and%20were%20entitled%20to%20contest%20and%20vote%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20before%202019.%20A%20number%20of%20PoJK%20refugees%20have%20been%20elected%20to%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20provisions%20in%20states%20and%20UTs%20on%20nominations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20legal%20provision%20for%20the%20nomination%20of%20MLAs%20in%20any%20state%20assembly.%20Such%20provisions%20only%20exist%20for%20the%20assemblies%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20Puducherry.%20All%20MLAs%20in%20the%20Delhi%20UT%20are%20elected%20by%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Sikkim%20assembly%2C%20there%20is%20a%20provision%20for%20the%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20Sikkimese%20people%20of%20Bhutia-Lepcha%20origin%20and%20Sanghas%20(Buddhist%20monastic%20community)%2C%20but%20elections%20are%20held%20on%20all%20seats%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEffective%20strength%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20assembly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20effective%20strength%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20assembly%20would%20be%2095%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20these%20seats.%20Ninety%20out%20of%2095%20members%20would%20be%20elected%20directly%20by%20the%20people%20and%20the%20remaining%20five%20would%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%2024%20seats%20will%20remain%20vacant%20in%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20assembly%20for%20the%20people%20living%20in%20areas%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20under%20the%20occupation%20of%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%93%20a%20provision%20in%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20constitution%20which%20was%20retained%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20when%20it%20reorganised%20J%26amp%3BK%20into%20two%20UTs%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%2024%20seats%20remain%20vacant%20and%20are%20not%20considered%20when%20calculating%20the%20total%20membership%20of%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUmer%20Maqbool%20is%20a%20Kashmir-based%20independent%20journalist.%20who%20writes%20on%20politics%2C%20governance%20and%20legal%20issues.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690210232000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F04090458%2F2022_10img03_Oct_2022_PTI10_03_.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Freservation-of-jk-assembly-seats-for-kashmiri-migrants-refugees-sparks-nomination-debate%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20proposed%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%20specifies%20that%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%93%20who%20is%20appointed%20by%20the%20