ers%E2%80%99%20Party%C2%A0(PSOE)%20had%C2%A033.1%25%C2%A0and%2031.7%25%20shares%20of%20the%20vote%C2%A0respectively%2C%20the%C2%A0results%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20give%20the%20PP%2C%20under%20leader%20Alberto%20Nunez%20Feijoo%2C%20136%C2%A0seats%20in%20the%20350-seat%C2%A0lower%20chamber%2C%20the%20Congress%20of%20Deputies%2C%20and%20the%20Socialists%C2%A0122%C2%A0seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EParties%20now%20look%20to%20form%20coalition%20government%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PP%20now%C2%A0requires%20support%20from%20several%20junior%20parties%C2%A0to%20achieve%C2%A0a%20governing%20majority%20of%20176%20seats%2C%20so%C2%A0the%20result%20is%20likely%20to%20produce%20weeks%20of%20political%20jockeying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20far-right%20Vox%2C%20which%20offered%20to%20partner%20with%20the%20PP%2C%20was%20projected%20to%20win%2033%20seats.%20But%20even%20with%20the%20169%20seats%20this%20would%20amount%20to%2C%20the%20PP%20would%20still%20be%20seven%20seats%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20that%20partnership%20is%20later%20confirmed%2C%20along%20with%20a%20third%20party%2C%20it%20would%20be%20the%20first%20time%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ffar-right-populism-in-europe%2Ft-66108914%5C%22%3Efar-right%20party%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20entered%20government%20in%20Spain%20since%20Francisco%20Franco%E2%80%99s%20dictatorship%20ended%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20radical%20left-wing%20Sumar%2C%20which%20brought%20together%2015%20small%20leftist%20parties%20and%C2%A0backed%20the%20Socialists%2C%20won%C2%A031%C2%A0seats%2C%20giving%20their%20alliance%20just%20153%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20remaining%20parties%20are%20mostly%20region-specific.%20The%20two%20Catalan%20pro-independence%20parties%2C%20who%20voted%20to%20support%20a%20Sanchez-lead%20government%20previously%2C%C2%A0saw%20their%20number%20of%20seats%20fall%2C%20but%20may%20still%20play%20the%20role%20of%20kingmaker%20if%20Sanchez%20tries%20to%20stay%20on%20as%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPossible%20demands%20from%20the%20separatist%20Catalan%20party%20Junts%20(Together)%20for%20a%20referendum%20on%20Catalonia%E2%80%99s%20independence%20could%20be%20an%20obstacle%20to%20Sanchez%20bringing%20it%20on%20board%20in%20a%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20failure%20by%20both%20sides%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20governing%20coalition%20could%20result%20in%20yet%20another%20election%20being%20called.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESanchez%20and%20Feijoo%20both%20claim%20victory%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PP%20leader%C2%A0told%20supporters%20in%20Madrid%20on%20Sunday%20evening%20that%20his%20party%20would%20now%20try%20to%20form%20a%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20candidate%20of%20the%20party%20that%20won%20the%20most%20seats%2C%20I%20believe%20it%20is%20my%20duty%20to%20try%20to%20form%20a%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20Feijoo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20asked%20that%20%E2%80%9Cno%20one%20fall%20into%20the%20temptation%20of%20blocking%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20new%20government%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20Spain%20did%20not%20need%20a%20period%20of%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanchez%20was%20also%20celebrating%20the%20result%C2%A0from%20the%20balcony%20of%20his%20party%20headquarters%20late%20Sunday%2C%20as%20the%20Socialists%20had%20won%C2%A0more%20seats%20and%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20the%20votes%20than%20in%20the%202019%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20supporters%20that%20the%20projected%20win%20of%20the%20conservative%20and%20far-right%20block%20had%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20backward-looking%20bloc%2C%20which%20proposed%20a%20total%20repeal%20of%20all%20the%20progress%20we%20have%20made%20over%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20has%20failed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20regressive%20block%20made%20up%20of%20the%20Popular%20Party%20and%20Vox%20were%20beaten.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20many%20more%20who%20want%20Spain%20to%20keep%20advancing%20than%20those%20who%20want%20to%20step%20backward%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sanchez%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20Spain%20hold%20a%20snap%20election%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fspain-to-hold-snap-general-election-in-july%2Fa-65762463%5C%22%3ESanchez%20called%20the%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%20early%20after%20the%20left%20took%20a%20drubbing%20in%20local%20elections%20in%20May.%20The%20vote%20was%20originally%20scheduled%20for%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20took%20place%C2%A0just%20three%20weeks%20after%20Spain%20took%20over%20the%20rotating%20presidency%20of%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20the%20PP%E2%80%99s%20win%20is%C2%A0a%20fresh%20blow%20to%20the%20European%20left%20after%20similar%20moves%20in%20other%20EU%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20Sweden%2C%20Finland%20and%20Italy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20also%20took%20place%20at%20the%20height%20of%20summer%2C%20when%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20voters%20may%20be%20away%20from%20their%20usual%20polling%20locations%20due%20to%20vacations%20and%20on%20the%20tail%20of%20a%20month%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fspain-saw-hottest-spring-on-record-in-2023%2Fa-65851473%5C%22%3Eheat%20waves%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurnout%20was%20calculated%20at%2070.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20record%20number%20%E2%80%93%202.47%20million%2C%20of%20the%2037.5%20million%20registered%20voters%20%E2%80%93%20cast%20an%20absentee%20ballot%20even%20before%20the%20polls%20opened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinor%20party%20poised%20to%20play%20kingmaker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPre-election%20polls%20had%20predicted%20a%20larger%20majority%20for%20the%C2%A0PP%20but%20that%20it%C2%A0would%20have%C2%A0to%20depend%20on%20Vox%E2%80%99s%C2%A0support%20to%20form%20a%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENunez%20Feijoo%20now%20needs%20to%20negotiate%20with%20much%20smaller%20parties%20to%20try%20to%20reach%20the%20176%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20published%20on%20Friday%20by%20%3Cem%3EEl%20Mundo%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Feijoo%20stated%20that%20a%20candidate%20should%20not%20disclose%20their%20alliances%20just%20two%20days%20before%20an%20election.%20He%20added%20a%20government%20with%20Vox%20%E2%80%9Cis%20not%20ideal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20PP%20and%20Vox%20have%20already%20teamed%20up%20to%20govern%20in%20dozens%20of%20regions%20and%20cities%20since%20local%20elections%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupport%20for%20the%20anti-Islam%2C%20anti-feminist%20party%20is%20on%C2%A0the%20wane.%C2%A0In%20the%20last%20election%20in%20November%202019%2C%20Vox%20won%2052%20seats.%20But%20Sunday%E2%80%99s%20election%20saw%20the%20far-right%20party%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20seats%20fall%20to%2033.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fspain-election-conservatives-win-but-fall-short-of-majority%2Fa-66321876%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690200577000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24173615%2FPP-Feijoo-X.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fspain-elections-conservatives-win-but-no-majority-yet%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20center-right%20Popular%20Party%20has%20beaten%20Prime%20Minister%20Pedro%20Sanchez'%20Socialists%2C%20but%20will%20need%20several%20junior%20parties%20to%20govern.%20The%20result%20is%20likely%20to%20spark%20weeks%20of%20political%20uncertainty.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fspain-elections-conservatives-win-but-no-majority-yet%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Same%20Sex%20Marriage%20Should%20Not%20Be%20Called%20an%20Urban%2C%20Elitist%20Demand%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201983%2C%20Justice%20H.R.%20Khanna%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20told%20those%20who%20try%20to%20preserve%20and%20protect%20the%20efficacy%20of%20fundamental%20rights%20have%20an%20elitist%20approach%E2%80%A6While%20listening%20to%20these%20exhortations%20we%20have%20to%20bear%20in%20mind%20that%20it%20were%20precisely%20these%20arguments%20which%20were%20adopted%20by%20those%20who%20set%20up%20totalitarian%20regimes%20by%20making%20a%20mockery%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitutions%20in%20some%20of%20the%20Afro-Asian%20countries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Furban-elitist-views-centre-files-affidavit-in-sc-opposing-same-sex-marriages%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eallegation%20of%20elitism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20specifically%20%E2%80%9Curban%20elitism%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20made%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20demand%20of%20same-sex%20marriage%20in%20an%20ongoing%20case%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20A%20similar%20allegation%20was%20made%20not%20long%20ago%20in%20the%20case%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findias-poor-must-right-privacy%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eright%20to%20privacy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Although%20the%20court%20brushed%20aside%20this%20argument%20in%20both%20the%20cases%2C%20it%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fright-to-privacy-supreme-court-2%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elikely%20to%20be%20invoked%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20future%20rights-based%20litigation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20appears%20compelling%20and%20has%20a%20strong%20appeal.%20The%20argument%20delegitimises%20a%20demand%20by%20indicating%20it%20to%20be%20a%20whim%20of%20privileged%20few.%20It%20raises%20the%20question%2C%20should%20the%20legislature%2Fcourts%20discuss%20such%20issues%20at%20all%20or%20is%20it%20a%20waste%20of%20time%3F%20Therefore%2C%20this%20argument%20of%20%E2%80%98urban%20elitism%E2%80%99%20deserves%20critical%20scrutiny.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20demand%20categorised%20as%20%E2%80%98elitist%E2%80%99%20implies%20that%20it%20comes%20from%20a%20%E2%80%98few%20privileged%E2%80%99%20sections.%20It%20is%20also%20deemed%20unnecessary%20by%20the%20larger%20lesser%20privileged%20sections%20who%20are%20burdened%20with%20the%20real%20issues%20of%20life.%20To%20suggest%20that%20a%20demand%20is%20%E2%80%9Curban%E2%80%9D%20implies%20that%20it%20is%20relevant%20to%20people%20in%20urban%20settings%20and%20irrelevant%20outside.%20The%20opposition%20to%20a%20supposed%20%E2%80%98urban%20elitist%E2%80%99%20demand%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20perceived%20irrelevance%20of%20such%20demands%20to%20human%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2F53-of-adults-in-india-support-legalisation-of-same-sex-marriages-finds-pew-research-center%5C%22%3E53%25%20of%20Adults%20in%20India%20Support%20Legalisation%20of%20Same-Sex%20Marriages%2C%20Finds%20Pew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20same-sex%20marriage%2C%20the%20argument%20of%20urban%20elitism%20gets%20frequently%20buttressed%20with%20visuals%20of%20people%20in%20burlesque%20costumes%20in%20urban%20settings.%20These%20visuals%20and%20arguments%20do%20not%20objectively%20explain%20the%20phenomena%20or%20further%20social%20or%20legal%20discourse.%20Instead%20they%20trivialise%20it%20and%20tend%20to%20arouse%20disdain%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20%E2%80%98othering%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModern%20science%20empirically%20recognises%20homosexuality%20as%20a%20naturally%20occurring%20phenomena%20across%20demographics%2C%20countries%20and%20cultures.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20operated%20on%20this%20understanding%20while%20deciding%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENavtej%20Jauhar%20v%20Union%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhere%20consensual%20sex%20among%20homosexuals%20was%20decriminalised%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESociologically%20urban%20spaces%20have%20always%20provided%20a%20sense%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ffuture%2Farticle%2F20170529-the-reasons-you-can-never-be-anonymous-again%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epersonal%20safety%20in%20anonymity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Large%20cities%20also%20give%20a%20sense%20of%20inclusion%20by%20sustaining%20small%20but%20sizable%20communities%20in%20otherwise%20diverse%20populations.%20Therefore%2C%20what%20seems%20like%20an%20%E2%80%9Curban%E2%80%9D%20demand%20is%20largely%20attributable%20to%20a%20sense%20of%20safety%20that%20facilitates%20expression%20of%20desire%20without%20fear%20of%20physical%20hurt%20or%20social%20ostracisation.%20It%20is%20not%20an%20urban%20demand%20but%20is%20often%20expressed%20freely%20in%20urban%20areas.%20The%20desire%20to%20marry%20exists%20irrespective%20of%20urban%20spaces%20and%2C%20thus%2C%20is%20not%20urban%20by%20nature.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20apparent%20occurrence%20of%20this%20demand%20in%20urban%20spaces%20is%20purely%20situational%20and%20not%20a%20causative%20factor%20for%20homosexuality%20or%20the%20desire%20to%20marry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20the%20desire%20to%20get%20married%20are%20not%20a%20function%20of%20wealth.%20It%20is%20another%20matter%20that%20the%20rich%20can%20afford%20to%20contest%20causes%20before%20the%20courts.%20They%20can%20take%20refuge%20in%20their%20private%20spaces%20and%20enjoy%20amenities.%20They%20can%20perhaps%20live%20with%20lesser%20social%20capital%20compared%20to%20those%20without%20financial%20security.%20People%20with%20resources%20are%20obviously%20able%20to%20raise%20their%20demand%20without%20fear%20of%20consequences%20that%20may%20become%20incumbent%20on%20the%20lesser%20privileged.%20Thus%2C%20creating%20the%20illusion%20that%20this%20demand%20comes%20from%20those%20who%20are%20rich.%20But%20it%20is%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20false%20correlation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EListen%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2Fmarriage-equality-onir-podcast%5C%22%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20Exhausting%20to%20See%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Aggression%20in%20the%20Same-Sex%20Marriage%20Case%3A%20Onir%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20contention%20was%20that%20only%20a%20few%20elites%20were%20concerned%20and%20their%20concerns%20were%20not%20shared%20by%20the%20majority.%20The%20court%20reasoned%20that%20such%20assertion%20was%20based%20on%20misunderstanding%20of%20the%20constitutional%20position.%20Our%20Constitution%20places%20the%20individual%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20its%20focus%2C%20guaranteeing%20civil%20and%20political%20rights%20in%20the%20Part%20III%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20begs%20another%20question.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20assume%20that%20a%20demand%20comes%20from%20a%20privileged%20few%20residing%20in%20urban%20spaces%20or%20any%20other%20cultural%2C%20linguistic%20or%20ethnic%20minority%20group.%20Should%20it%20be%20rejected%20merely%20because%20the%20people%20demanding%20it%20are%20fewer%20in%20number%20and%20others%20do%20not%20share%20their%20concern%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20larger%20numbers%20create%20political%20outcomes%2C%20the%20law%20always%20protects%20the%20individual%20and%20minority%20so%20that%20they%20can%20have%20an%20equal%20participation%20in%20society.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20legality%20of%20demands%20cannot%20be%20assessed%20in%20terms%20of%20numerical%20strength%20but%20within%20the%20confines%20of%20legal%20principles.%20Numbers%20are%20relevant%20in%20assessing%20political%20support.%20Characterisation%20of%20a%20demand%20as%20urban%20elitist%20often%20places%20reliance%20on%20political%20support%20than%20legal%20merit%20of%20that%20demand.%20In%20a%20democracy%20committed%20to%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20such%20logic%20has%20never%20found%20favour%20with%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EArjun%20Harkauli%20and%20Aditya%20Pratap%20Singh%20Rathore%20are%20lawyers%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690199402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2Fwhy-same-sex-marriage-should-not-be-called-an-urban-elitist-demand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20desire%20to%20marry%20exists%20irrespective%20of%20urban%20spaces%20and%2C%20thus%2C%20is%20not%20urban%20by%20nature.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2Fwhy-same-sex-marriage-should-not-be-called-an-urban-elitist-demand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Guntur%20Kaaram%3A%20PS%20Vinod%20walks%20out%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690199237000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102081347%2Cimgsize-128306.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftelugu%2Fmovies%2Fnews%2Fmahesh-babus-guntur-kaaram-ps-vinod-walks-out-thaman-replaced-heres-what-we-know%2Farticleshow%2F102081347.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%2