ite-off-bad-loans-worth-rs-2-09-lakh-crore-in-2022-23-rbi-8856435%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBanks%2520wrote%2520off%2520bad%2520loans%2Cto%2520Information%2520(RTI)%2520reply.%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20reply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20the%20total%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20the%20banking%20sector%20to%20a%20significant%20Rs%2010.57%20lakh%20crore%20(around%20%24129%20billion)%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20write-offs%20have%20helped%20banks%20to%20bring%20down%20gross%20non-performing%20assets%20(GNPA)%20%E2%80%93%20or%20loans%20defaulted%20by%20borrowers%20%E2%80%93%20to%20a%2010-year%20low%20of%203.9%25%20of%20advances%20in%20March%202023%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGross%20NPAs%20of%20banks%20had%20fallen%20from%20Rs%2010.21%20lakh%20crore%20in%20FY2018%20to%20Rs%205.55%20lakh%20crore%20by%20March%202023%2C%20mainly%20on%20the%20back%20of%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20RBI%20data%2C%20banks%20have%20written%20off%20Rs%2015%2C31%2C453%20crore%20(%24187%20billion)%20since%20FY2012-13.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20loans%20written%20off%20by%20banks%20will%20remain%20in%20the%20books%20of%20banks%20as%20unrecovered%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%E2%80%99s%20RTI%20reply%20said%20banks%20recovered%20only%20Rs%20109%2C186%20crore%20from%20Rs%20586%2C891%20crore%20loans%20written%20off%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20could%20only%20recover%2018.60%25%20of%20the%20write-offs%20during%20the%20three-year%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20defaulted%20loans%20(including%20write-offs%20but%20excluding%20loans%20recovered%20from%20write-offs%20in%20three%20years)%20amount%20to%20Rs%2010.32%20lakh%20crore%2C%20the%20daily%20reported%2C%20citing%20the%20back%20of%20the%20envelope%20calculation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20NPA%20ratio%2C%20including%20write-offs%2C%20would%20have%20become%207.47%25%20of%20advances%20as%20against%203.9%25%20reported%20by%20the%20banks%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20fiscal%20ended%20March%202023%2C%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20banks%20rose%20to%20Rs%20209%2C144%20crore%2C%20as%20against%20Rs%20174%2C966%20crore%20a%20year%20ago%20in%20March%202022%2C%20and%20Rs%20202%2C781%20crore%20in%20March%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbysmal%20recoveries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanks%20write%20off%20loans%20to%20reduce%20NPAs%20in%20their%20books%2C%20however%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20note%20that%20they%20have%20reported%20abysmal%20recoveries%20from%20the%20written%20off%20loans.%20The%20newspaper%20reported%20that%20they%20could%20recover%20only%20Rs%2030%2C104%20crore%20in%20FY21%2C%20Rs%2033%2C534%20crore%20in%20FY22%20and%20Rs%2045%2C548%20crore%20in%20FY23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20banking%20analyst%20to%20%3Cem%3EIE%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3EAfter%20write-off%2C%20banks%20are%20supposed%20to%20continue%20their%20efforts%20to%20recover%20the%20loan%20using%20various%20options.%20They%20have%20to%20make%20provisioning%20also.%20The%20tax%20liability%20will%20also%20come%20down%20as%20the%20written%20off%20amount%20is%20reduced%20from%20the%20profit.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20loan%20is%20classified%20as%20an%20NPA%20when%20the%20repayment%20of%20the%20principal%20amount%20or%20the%20interest%20remains%20outstanding%20for%20a%20period%20of%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20identity%20of%20these%20borrowers%20was%20never%20revealed%20by%20banks%20or%20the%20RBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20individual%20banks%2C%20reduction%20in%20NPAs%20due%20to%20write-offs%20in%20the%20case%20of%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20was%20Rs%2024%2C061%20crore%20in%20FY2023%2C%20Punjab%20National%20Bank%20Rs%2016%2C578%20crore%2C%20Union%20Bank%20Rs%2019%2C175%20crore%2C%20Central%20Bank%20of%20India%20Rs%2010%2C258%20crore%20and%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20Rs%2017%2C998%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20substantial%20portion%20of%20this%20write-off%20is%2C%20however%2C%20technical%20in%20nature.%20It%20is%20primarily%20intended%20at%20cleansing%20the%20balance%20sheet%20and%20achieving%20taxation%20efficiency.%20In%20%E2%80%98Technically%20Written%20Off%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98%20accounts%2C%20loans%20are%20written%20off%20from%20the%20books%20at%20the%20Head%20Office%2C%20without%20foregoing%20the%20right%20to%20recovery.%20Further%2C%20write-offs%20are%20generally%20carried%20out%20against%20accumulated%20provisions%20made%20for%20such%20loans.%20Once%20recovered%2C%20the%20provisions%20made%20for%20those%20loans%20flow%20back%20into%20the%20profit%20and%20loss%20account%20of%20banks%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20central%20bank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fbanking-and-finance%2Fpsu-banks-write-off-rs-55356-crore-in-six-months-bad-debt-4966594%2F%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20loan%20recovery%20process%20can%20take%20years%20as%20most%20of%20the%20loans%20involved%20in%20write-offs%20belong%20to%20wilful%20defaulters%20and%20promoters%20who%20generally%20don%E2%80%99t%20pay%20back%20to%20the%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20non-transparent%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20without%20any%20policy.%20There%E2%80%99s%20possibility%20of%20wrong-doing.%20Generally%2C%20write-off%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20small%2C%20used%20sparingly%20when%20there%E2%80%99s%20some%20crisis.%20Technical%20write-off%20creates%20non-transparency%2C%20destroys%20the%20credit%20risk%20management%20system%20and%20brings%20all%20types%20of%20wrong-doings%20into%20the%20system.%20You%20must%20declare%20how%20much%20you%E2%80%99re%20writing%20off.%20You%E2%80%99re%20writing%20off%20public%20money.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20scandal.%20You%E2%80%99re%20writing%20off%20public%20money%20you%E2%80%99re%20not%20acknowledging%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20RBI%20official%20told%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690194622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F07182915%2Frbi_pti.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbad-loans-npas-written-off-rbi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Banks%20could%20recover%20only%20Rs%2030%2C104%20crore%20in%20FY21%2C%20Rs%2033%2C534%20crore%20in%20FY22%20and%20Rs%2045%2C548%20crore%20in%20FY23%2C%20as%20per%20RBI's%20reply%20to%20the%20Indian%20Express's%20RTI%20queries.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A150%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbad-loans-npas-written-off-rbi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World%20record%20bid%20made%20for%20Mbappe%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690194060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F70x70%2Fskynews-kylian-mbappe-goal_6228760.jpg%3F20230724120128%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fkylian-mbappe-saudi-team-al-hilal-make-world-record-163259m-bid-for-psg-striker-12926565%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Saudi%20football%20club%20Al%20Hilal%20have%20made%20a%20world%20record%20%C2%A3259m%20bid%20for%C2%A0Paris%20Saint-Germain%C2%A0striker%C2%A0Kylian%20Mbappe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1778%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fkylian-mbappe-saudi-team-al-hilal-make-world-record-259m-bid-for-psg-striker-12926565%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fkylian-mbappe-saudi-team-al-hilal-make-world-record-259m-bid-for-psg-striker-12926565%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fkylian-mbappe-saudi-team-al-hilal-make-world-record-259m-bid-for-psg-striker-12926565%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IDBI%20Bank%20Q1%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20jumps%20by%2062%25%20YoY