ty-rare-disease-research%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epatients%20with%20malaria%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20bring%20them%20back%20to%20Ross%E2%80%99%20lab.%20Here%2C%20the%20latter%20would%20collect%20blood%20samples%20from%20these%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20real-time%20experiments%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20boost%20for%20Ross%E2%80%99%20research.%20And%20by%201899%2C%20he%20had%20not%20only%20discovered%20the%20role%20of%20the%20female%20Anopheles%20mosquito%20as%20a%20vector%20in%20the%20transmission%20of%20malaria%20to%20humans%20but%20also%20stumbled%20upon%20the%20transmission%20cycle%20of%20the%20disease%20in%20birds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20missing%20acknowledgement%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20657px)%20100vw%2C%20657px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F310404072_499624505511134_3279398283006220694_n-1689681959.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22657%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kishori%20Mohan%20Bandyopadhyay%2C%20the%20Indian%20scientist%20who%20greatly%20contributed%20to%20the%20discovery%20of%20transmission%20of%20malaria%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F310404072_499624505511134_3279398283006220694_n-1689681959.jpg%20657w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F310404072_499624505511134_3279398283006220694_n-1689681959-246x300.jpg%20246w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F310404072_499624505511134_3279398283006220694_n-1689681959-500x609.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F310404072_499624505511134_3279398283006220694_n-1689681959-150x183.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324196%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKishori%20Mohan%20Bandyopadhyay%2C%20th